tspan.tspan: Supplemental Figure Y: host genotype differentiation of skin microbiome. A) Change of alpha diversity (Faith's Phylogenetic Diversity) over
generations. Diversity of five individual embryo recipient mother (RM) mice of mixed genotype B6CF1 (gray), housed in three cages is given
as the red box and circles. Following line plots summarize the diversity of six offspring generations (P to F5), which were inbreed in three
fully separated cage lineages per genotype (C57BL6/J in blue and BALB/c in orange). Diversity of three to five control mice per genotype and
per independent environments (Duesseldorf and Janvier) is visualized as four boxes and circles on the right hand side. Top x axis labels
indicate number of individual mice (i), number of cages (c) in which mice were housed and number of cage lineages (l). B) Beta diversity
distance (measured as unweighted UniFrac) to RM samples. Line plots summarize distance of C57BLK6/J and BALB/C samples to RM
samples, in blue and orange, respectively. Green line plot indicates distance between both genotypes. For reference, the gray dashed line is
the mean pairwise distance between individuals housed in the same cage, i.e. lower resolution limit as these mice should be biological
replicates. Brown dotted line is the mean distance of individuals from two different cages (963 individual pairs: i-i) of the same genotype,
cage lineage and generation. Significance is assessed via PERMANOVA tests with 999 permutations. C) Beta diversity distance (measured as
unweighted UniFrac) to control samples as a proxy of environment. Solid lines stand for control mice from Duesseldorf (Germany), dashed
lines from Janvier (France). D) Microbiome distance (measured as unweighted UniFrac) between offspring and true dam (blue and orange
boxes for C57BL6/J and BALB/c, respectively) and between offspring and dam of same genotype but different cage lineage (gray boxes) and
between offspring and dam of the other genotype (green boxes). E)
Source Tracker Anna
. We used Mann-Whitney-Wilcoxon for all statistical
tests with Benjamini-Hochberg correction for multiple testing (ns: not significant, ****: p ≤ 0.0001, ***: p ≤ 0.001, **: p ≤ 0.01, * p ≤ 0.05,
annotations in brackets indicate either tests with too few sample numbers or tests whoes p-values reach significance niveau but their
corrected q-values do not.)
